fb88-4519-b4b0-870f3c4de7db?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXe=
pKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] , Pete Billington [ https://link.sbstck.com/redirect/=
5e2016de-9bc3-4d25-bdde-714e35582439?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNu=
aMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], Jessica Yaffa-Shamash [ https://link.sbstck=
=2Ecom/redirect/0eb8b186-157d-413a-b6c=
1-b3d15ff9540a?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.g=
b8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
We present our approach to generating high-quality episodic content for IP'=
s (Intellectual Property) using large language models (LLMs), custom state-=
of-the art diffusion models and our multi-agent simulation for contextualiz=
ation, story progression and behavioral control. Powerful LLMs such as GPT-=
4 were trained on a large corpus of TV show data which lets us believe that=
 with the right guidance users will be able to rewrite entire seasons.
The team at Fable Simulations just created an entire South Park episode tha=
t was actually a little bit funny with AI. I could explain it, but you shou=
ld just watch it.=20
(2) Meta and Microsoft Introduce the Next Generation of Llama [ https://lin=
k.sbstck.com/redirect/bd407483-8fe7-4b45-9c59-b8cd807d0789?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAw=
Z3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
From Meta
We=E2=80=99re now ready to open source the next version of Llama 2 and are =
making it available free of charge for research and commercial use [ https:=
//link.sbstck.com/redirect/fe5598c7-fe60-43a7-ac59-791a1b90aeaa?j=3DeyJ1Ijo=
iOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]. We=E2=80=99re in=
cluding model weights and starting code for the pretrained model and conver=
sational fine-tuned versions too. As Satya Nadella announced on stage at Mi=
crosoft Inspire, we=E2=80=99re taking our partnership to the next level wit=
h Microsoft as our preferred partner for Llama 2 and expanding our efforts =
in generative AI.
Zuck. So hot right now, Zuck.
Meta is open sourcing its LLM, Llama 2, and doing so in close partnership w=
ith Microsoft. This announcement is significant for a couple of reasons:
Now anyone can build on top of Llama 2, for free. And since the models are =
open to builders, they=E2=80=99ll get improved, fixed, and stress-tested mo=
re quickly.=20
Within the announcement, it was revealed that Llama 2 is approaching (and i=
n some areas beating) other LLM (like GPT 3.5) benchmarks. This means that =
Meta is open sourcing a LLM just about as powerful as any closed LLM in the=
 world. Still not at the same level as GPT4, but we=E2=80=99ll see how open=
 sourcing this changes that over time.
Meta is doing all of this in partnership with Microsoft. This is a win for =
Microsoft=E2=80=99s Azure business, an LLM diversification hedge, and a str=
ong alliance against Google.
Right now it seems like Zuck and Satya are operating on different levels th=
an their Big Tech counterparts, and doing so in ways that benefit developer=
s and end-users.=20
(3) Energy Startup Says It Has Achieved Geothermal Tech Breakthrough [ http=
s://link.sbstck.com/redirect/548ba658-705f-4b9e-9b5b-b621a6d1c33e?j=3DeyJ1I=
joiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Michelle Ma [ https://link.sbstck.com/redirect/11d070b1-53ef-4e34-9077-5782=
90cb3b9b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU=
 ] for Bloomberg
In a landmark step for enhanced geothermal technology=E2=80=99s potential a=
s a dependable carbon-free energy source, startup Fervo Energy has complete=
d a performance demonstration of its commercial pilot. Geothermal power pla=
nts are carbon-free and can operate any time, making them a critical part o=
f a 100% carbon-free electric grid.
Over the past couple of months, we=E2=80=99ve written a fair amount about n=
ew (and rapidly progressing) renewable energy technologies. One area that w=
e haven=E2=80=99t covered much is geothermal. Geothermal harnesses the heat=
 inside the earth to produce energy. Think of a geothermal power plant like=
 a giant tea kettle and the heat inside the earth as a giant stove.
Geothermal is promising because it=E2=80=99s a dependable (there will alway=
s be heat inside the earth!) carbon-free energy source. However, like so ma=
ny promising technologies, geothermal has always been a few years away from=
 being a few years away. The technology simply wasn=E2=80=99t there yet to =
commercialize geothermal at scale.
However, this breakthrough from Fervo accelerates previous consensus timeli=
nes on geothermal. At its Utah site alone, the company is now predicting it=
 will produce 400 megawatts by 2028, enough to power 300,000 homes. Even pr=
ior to that, Fervo produced energy will power Google data centers as early =
as later this year.
Things are starting to..umm..heat up in renewables!
(4) Donanemab in Early Symptomatic Alzheimer DiseaseThe TRAILBLAZER-ALZ 2 R=
andomized Clinical Trial [ https://link.sbstck.com/redirect/77d8d480-b8d2-4=
441-ab26-b9737c1c0fc3?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOs=
a8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
John R.=C2=A0Sims,=C2=A0MD [ https://link.sbstck.com/redirect/a42ead40-56e1=
-47e2-84dd-d64ea32e227d?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbq=
